    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="548"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/2–2045</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Spanish Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lequerica</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the American Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Buttemoorth</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="85" xml:id="d548fn85">Copy transmitted to the Department in
                        despatch 4070, February 20, 1945; received March 6.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-19">February 19,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Chargé d’affaires</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                    the receipt of your Note of today’s date, in which you communicate to me the
                    terms of a Protocol additional to the Air Transportation Agreement between the
                    Spanish Government and the Government of the United <pb facs="0742" n="730"
                        xml:id="pg_730"/> States of America signed in Madrid on December 2, 1944, a
                    Protocol which has been agreed to in the negotiations now concluded between both
                    governments.</p>
                <p>The terms of the said Protocol which Your Honor has communicated to me are the
                    following:</p>
                <p>[Here follow the terms of the Protocol as given in note No. 3801, printed <hi
                        rend="italic">supra</hi>.]</p>
                <p>I have instructions to inform Your Honor that my Government accepts the terms of
                    the Protocol in the form in which they have been communicated to me, and
                    likewise that it agrees with Your Honor’s proposal that the said Protocol enter
                    into effect on February 19, 1945, considering it therefore as being in force
                    from the indicated date.</p>
                <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lequerica</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
